  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink273-kilavi">varaiviṭai vaittup piriyum talaimakaṉ niṉ tuṇaiviyai yuṭampaṭuvittēṉ, iṉi nīyē yitaṟk uṭampaṭātu kaliḻkiṉṟāy eṉṟāṟkut tōḻi kūṟiyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> 
          What the confidante said to the hero who, having fixed the time for marriage and was [about to] separate, said, “I have made your companion consent; now you alone, not consenting to this, are weeping.”
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink273">
<l>attac ceyalait tuppuṟa ḻoṇṭaḷir</l>
<l>puṉṟalai manti vaṉpaṟa ḻāru</l>
<l>naṉmalai nāṭa nīceli</l>
<l>ṉiṉṉayan tuṟaivi yeṉṉiṉuṅ kaliḻmē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from the land of the good mountain,</l>
        <l>where the strong young one of the ruddy-headed female monkey</l>
        <l>fills [itself] with the bright shoots of the aśoka trees along the way,</l>
        <l>which resemble red coral—</l>
        <l>if you go,</l>
        <l>she who remains longing for you</l>
        <l>will weep even more than I do!</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
